        		<marginalia hand="Italian">
        			<language ident="LA">
        				<position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    				<marginalia_text>
                    					Multa Specula Cristallina : sed paucissima adamantina.  
                    				</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        			</language>
        			<translation>
        				Many mirrors are crystalline: but very few are adamantine. 
        			</translation>
        		</marginalia>
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Christus nec ullis ipse egebat libris: nec vllum Apostolis comme[n]dauit,
    						orbem terraru[m] superare
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<person name="Apostles"/>
    					<person name="Jesus Christ"/>
    				</position>
    				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						) cogitantibus.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Christ himself did not need any books: nor did he recommend a single book to the Apostles who were intent on transcending the world.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Spiritu, et industria quid non? sed utroq[ue] singulari.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>			
    			<translation>
    				Why not by spirit and industry? But with each being singular.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Et musca[e] suus est splen: et vespa[e] sua	
    						bilis. ( Martyres apostoli: sed inoffensi.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				The fly has his spleen: and the wasp has his bile. 
    				(   The apostles are martyrs: but unhindered.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Sed liberatus est insanus, qui prudens
    						( est incarceratus.    						
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				The madman is free, while whoever is prudent is imprisoned.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="270">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Incomparabilis est Spiritus, Industria, Peritia; qua[e] maximaru[m] reru[m].
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    				<position place="intext" book_orientation="270">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						potitur.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Incomparable is the Spirit, Industry, Experience; which becomes master of the greatest matters.
    				
